query: How many transactions were made by customers who have a loan?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM transactions 
WHERE acc_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT accounts.id 
    FROM accounts 
    WHERE cus_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT loans.cus_id FROM loans)
);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
RETURN count(t) AS transaction_count

query: What is the total balance of accounts belonging to customers who also have a deposit?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(acc.acc_bal) as total_balance FROM accounts acc JOIN deposits dep ON acc.cus_id = dep.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
RETURN SUM(a.account_balance) AS total_balance

query: What is the number of customers who have both a loan and a deposit?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT c.id) AS num_customers_with_both_loan_and_deposit
FROM customers c
JOIN deposits d ON c.id = d.cus_id
JOIN loans l ON c.id = l.cus_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans), (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)
RETURN COUNT(DISTINCT c) AS numberOfCustomersWithLoanAndDeposit

query: What is the total loan balance for customers who own at least one card?
sql_command: SELECT SUM(loans.bal) AS total_loan_balance FROM loans WHERE loans.cus_id IN (SELECT DISTINCT cards.cus_id FROM cards);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(cards:Cards)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(loans:Loans)
RETURN SUM(loans.balance) AS total_loan_balance

query: What is the total deposit balance for customers who made at least one transaction?
sql_command:
SELECT SUM(d.bal) AS total_deposit_balance 
FROM deposits d
WHERE d.cus_id IN (
    SELECT DISTINCT c.id 
    FROM customers c
    JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
    JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id
);
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
RETURN SUM(a.account_balance) AS total_deposit_balance

query: How many transactions were made by customers who belong to branch 1?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(t.id) AS transaction_count
FROM transactions t
JOIN accounts a ON t.acc_id = a.id
JOIN customers c ON a.cus_id = c.id
WHERE c.brc = 1;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]->(b:Branches {branch_id: 1})<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
RETURN count(t) AS transaction_count

query: What is the total number of accounts for customers who belong to each branch?
sql_command:
SELECT b.brc, COUNT(a.id) as total_accounts
FROM branches b
JOIN customers c ON b.id = c.brc
JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
GROUP BY b.brc
ORDER BY total_accounts DESC;
cypher_command: MATCH (c:Customers)-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]->(b:Branches)<-[:BELONGS_TO_BRANCH]-(a:Accounts) WITH b.branch_id AS branch_id, COUNT(a) AS total_accounts RETURN branch_id, total_accounts

query: What is the number of customers with more than one account?
sql_command: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cus_id) FROM accounts GROUP BY cus_id HAVING COUNT(acc_num) > 1;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WITH c, COUNT(a) AS accountCount
WHERE accountCount > 1
RETURN COUNT(c) AS numberOfCustomersWithMultipleAccounts

query: What is the number of customers with more than one loan?

query: What is the number of customers with more than one deposit?

query: What is the number of blocked cards belonging to customers with loans?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(cards.id) AS blocked_card_count
FROM cards
JOIN customers ON cards.cus_id = customers.id
JOIN loans ON customers.id = loans.cus_id
WHERE cards.is_blocked = true;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)<-[:HAS_LOAN_TYPE]-(lt:LoanTypes),
      (c)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE card.is_blocked = true
RETURN count(card) AS blocked_card_count

query: What is the number of expired cards belonging to customers with deposits?
sql_command:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS expired_card_count
FROM cards c
JOIN customers cu ON c.cus_id = cu.id
JOIN deposits d ON cu.id = d.cus_id
WHERE c.card_exp_date < CURRENT_DATE;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(d:Deposits)<-[:HAS_DEPOSIT_TYPE]-(a:Accounts)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(card:Cards)
WHERE date(card.expiration_date) < date()
RETURN count(card) AS expired_card_count

query: What is the number of accounts created before 2020 for customers with loans?

cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(l:Loans)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)
WHERE date(a.created_at) < date('2020-01-01')
RETURN count(a) AS numberOfAccounts

query: What is the number of customers who have all four: accounts, loans, deposits, and cards?

query: What is the total transaction amount for customers who own more than one account?
sql_command:
SELECT SUM(t.tran_amt) AS total_transaction_amount
FROM customers c
JOIN accounts a ON c.id = a.cus_id
JOIN (
  SELECT cus_id
  FROM accounts
  GROUP BY cus_id
  HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT acc_num) > 1
) multiple_accounts ON c.id = multiple_accounts.cus_id
JOIN transactions t ON a.id = t.acc_id;
cypher_command:
MATCH (c:Customers)<-[:BELONGS_TO_CUSTOMER]-(a:Accounts)<-[:HAS_TRANSACTION]-(t:Transactions)
WITH c, COUNT(a) AS account_count, SUM(t.transaction_amount) AS total_transaction_amount
WHERE account_count > 1
RETURN total_transaction_amount

query: What is the total number of deposits for customers with more than one loan?
